data.enText: the money system of Britain, based on the pound

data.chText: 可以付你英镑，也可以付你美元。
data.enText: You can be paid in pounds sterling or American dollars.

data.chText: 他在财务委员会工作优异。
data.enText: He has done sterling work on the finance committee.

tr: especially the pound sterling as the basic monetary unit of the UK

value.def: Sterling is the money system of Great Britain.

example.ex: The stamps had to be paid for in sterling.
example.tran: 这些邮票必须用英镑购买。

value.def: Sterling means very good in quality; used to describe someone's work or character.

example.ex: Those are sterling qualities to be admired in anyone.
example.tran: 那些是在任何人身上都值得敬佩的优秀品质。
他多年出色的工作表现

value.tran: (人的品格或工作)优异的，出色的

trans: 标准纯银(达到规定的纯度)
